calls_data2 = mutate(calls_data, responsetime = as.numeric(difftime(calls_data$timearrive,calls_data$timecreate, units="hours")))
calls_data2 = mutate(calls_data2, responsetime_normalized = 276-calls_data2$responsetime)
calls_data2

276 was the highest response time, so responsetime_normalized is basically 276-responsetime and response time is in hours

67A - Auto theft 20 - Auto Accident 62B - Business Burglary 62R - Residence Burglary

response time for auto theft is pretty consistent among all zip codes (less than 24 hours) except for 70130 and 70114, 70131, 70112, 70128 which takes more that 75 hours (roughly more than 3 days) and 70126, 70129 (roughly 2 days)

response time for all auto accidents in all zip codes are roughly the same around a little bit less than 48 hours or 2 days

response time for business burglary in all zip codes are roughly the same at around 60 hours or 2.5 days

response time for residence burglary in all zip codes are roughly the same at around 87 hours or 3.6 days

response time for discharged firearm in all zip codes are roughly the same at around 36 hours or 1.5 days
